<HEADLINE>
FT  29 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Cambridge Water
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Peter Shaw, chairman of Cambridge Water, said that water resources, much
depleted in the four-year 'drought', had now recovered to near-average
levels.
The statutory water company announced profits ahead to Pounds 1.77m pre-tax
for the six months to September 30, against Pounds 1.69m last time. Turnover
improved to Pounds 7.63m (Pounds 7.23m).
Earnings per Pounds 1 share worked through at 394p (410p); the interim
dividend goes up 10p to 65p.
