<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
European shipowners yesterday sought to defuse a dispute with their
customers over freight rates across the North Atlantic, writes Charles
Batchelor in London.
European Union ministers will later today review a special exemption granted
to shipowners which allows them to group together in 'conferences' to agree
prices on certain routes. Belgium, as president of the European Union, is
expected tofile a motion confirming the exemption for conferences.
