<HEADLINE>
FT  29 NOV 93 / Israelis attack bases in Lebanon
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Foreign Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Israeli helicopter gunships attacked two Palestinian bases in Lebanon
yesterday, while further shooting erupted in the occupied Gaza strip, writes
Our Foreign Staff.
Two helicopters fired missiles at bases of two radical Damascus-based
Palestinian groups at a refugee camp near Sidon, wounding three people. It
was the fifth Israeli air raid over south Lebanon since the
Israeli-Palestinian accord was signed in September.
Palestinians in Gaza said Israeli troops shot dead an activist from the
PLO's Fatah faction in a gunfight. In a separate incident the Israeli army
said one of its soldiers was wounded when shots were fired at an army post
in Gaza City.
The violence came as Israeli ministers played down talk of a crisis in talks
with the PLO on the planned self-rule for Gaza and the Jericho area of the
West Bank.
