<HEADLINE>
FT  27 NOV 93 / Finance and the Family: Nationwide's new bond - At a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nationwide's new escalating three-year Fixed Growth Bond will pay 5.5 per
cent gross in the first six months, rising to 7.5 per cent gross in the last
six months. Those closing the account in years 2 and 3 will lose 180 days'
interest.
Britannia's Guaranteed Reversal bond pays a variable rate which changes by
half a percentage point with every half point chnage in bank base rates.
Base rates at 5.5 per cent attract interest at 6 per cent gross. The maximum
interest rate is 7.5 per cent gross (base rates at 4 per cent) and the
minimum is 5.5 per cent (base rates at 6.5 per cent).
The bond matures on October 1 1994.
The minimum investment in both building society bonds is Pounds 5,000.
Portman is paying a fixed rate of 6.5 per cent gross for six months (or 6
per cent for one year) on a minimum deposit of Pounds 500. It will withdraw
the bond on Tuesday.
