<HEADLINE>
FT  27 NOV 93 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Complete lack of activity during the past fortnight has brought a weaker
market for all grades of black and white pepper, reports Man Producten. In
spite of the relatively low stocks everywhere more selling pressure has
accumulated lately and prices started to drop faster, especially for white
pepper. White muntok pepper is being offered at Dollars 2,800 a tonne, cif,
and black pepper grade 1 can be bought at Dollars 1,400, cif. White is
certainly still overvalued whereas the opposite is true for black.
November 26 - COMEX, CSCE, NYCE and NYMEX markets closed.
</TEXT>
